caption.body: #OnThisDay in 1960, the Pan American Worldport terminal opened at Idlewild Airport, now called John F. Kennedy International Airport in New York City. #PanAm operated out of the Worldport terminal until the airline ceased operations in 1991. Delta Airlines took over  Worldport until May of 2013; the terminal was demolished the following month. These two pictures, taken in 1959, show the construction of the  Worldport terminal. Did you ever fly out of the Worldport terminal?  Idlewild Airport, Pan American World Airways Worldport under construction 1959 SFO Museum Collection Gift of David Armstrong Abercrombie 2015.037.040
